This place is unprofessional and unsanitary. I ordered a Dukem Combo and deserts for pickup from here since DC is full of Ethiopian Restaurants and I’d like to try them all. I’m convinced I was given leftovers since the dish was not warm at all. The greens, cabbage, and minchet abesh (looked like cat food or canned tuna) had a “rinsed off” taste. It was all very tasteless. The doro wot was very well seasoned, but once I started to chew it, it was very tough and dry. Back home, those of us eating were trying to be polite by and gave it a good try but we looked at each other and agreed we didn’t like it and could not do it anymore. I called Dukem and told them that I think we got a bad batch and asked if it was possible to get a remake. The person on the phone didn’t listen to anything else I had to say and said the order was already picked up by UberEats and there isn’t a way they could fix it and I was hung up on, or so he thought. I heard them mocking me for a moment before I decided to make the second trip across town to reason with them in-person. I arrived and presented my receipt and the box of food and said the order was not good. A woman in the kitchen was the only person I could see without a mask began yelling at me asking if I have ever eaten Ethiopian food before, and told me she would not be accommodating me at all. I asked her to lower her voice to speak about how truly subpar the food was and she started flailing her hands and yelled louder to tell me that I should not have tried all the food. I was not able to be heard and after looking around at other guests, I left the food there and was too hungry to spend anymore time not making Plan B for dinner at 9:30pm. As an Ethiopian food lover will never return, I will stick with what I know and avoid Dukem at all cost. The baklava and  tiramisu were great!

When I went to let them know I was dissatisfied with the food, the lady working in the back came out without a mask on (mind you this is during the COVID—19 epidemic) and starts yelling at me (again this is without a mask). So the food was a 1/5. The customer service was a 0/5. If I could give this restaurant ZERO stars I would. I’m so disappointed in this place and I will never return again.

It's been a few years since I've been to Dukem and it's really lost something. The gf and I went there tonight and had a number of issues:  1. The yellow lentils on our plate tasted as if they had gone bad. They were happy to give us another item but, come on, that can't happen.  2. They charged us $1.50 for an additional piece of injeera. I can understand an up charge if we were requesting a substantial amount extra but they had only given us one piece between us to share. Also, neither pieces of our injeera were warm. I know that Ethiopian food is often served at room temperature, as ours was, but usually the injeera has been held on a steamer.  3. The flavors on the whole were underwhelming. I don't have specific complaints here but they just weren't as robust as other Ethiopian places I love like Ethiopic or Habesha.  4. A non-food related issue was the fact that it was freezing. They did sit us next to the windows overlooking the patio so perhaps it was better in other areas of the restaurant but they should really consider improved insulation in that area during the winter.  On the whole, I'd say that with the number of Ethiopian places, both in the city, and in Silver Spring you're better off elsewhere.
